dcterms:description: The PICMUS dataset comprises two simulation sets, two in vitro sets, and two in vivo sets, all acquired using a 128-element L11â€“4v linear-array transducer. The dataset is utilized for evaluating ultrasound imaging techniques.
dcterms:title: PICMUS dataset

dcterms:creator: J. Jensen
N. Svendsen
dcterms:description: The SC dataset is a simulation dataset designed to evaluate the contrast in ultrasound imaging, featuring images with a total of 9 anechoic regions against a speckle background.
dcterms:title: SC (Simulation Contrast)

dcterms:creator: J. Jensen
dcterms:description: The SR dataset is a simulation dataset aimed at assessing spatial resolution in ultrasound imaging, featuring images with point targets distributed against an anechoic background.
dcterms:title: SR (Simulation Resolution)

dcterms:creator: H. Liebgott
A. Rodriguez-Molares
F. Cervenansky
J. Jensen
O. Bernard
dcterms:description: The ER dataset is an experimental dataset used to evaluate both spatial resolution and contrast in ultrasound imaging, featuring images with point targets and a hyperechoic region against a speckle background.
dcterms:title: ER (Experimental Resolution)

dcterms:creator: H. Liebgott
A. Rodriguez-Molares
F. Cervenansky
J. Jensen
O. Bernard
dcterms:description: The EC dataset is an experimental dataset designed to evaluate contrast in ultrasound imaging, featuring images with two anechoic regions against a speckle background.
dcterms:title: EC (Experimental Contrast)

dcterms:description: The CC dataset consists of carotid cross-sectional images acquired from the carotid artery of a volunteer, used for evaluating ultrasound imaging techniques.
dcterms:title: CC (Carotid Cross)

dcterms:description: The CL dataset consists of carotid longitudinal images acquired from the carotid artery of a volunteer, used for evaluating ultrasound imaging techniques.
dcterms:title: CL (Carotid Long)

dcterms:description: The additional in vivo dataset comprises five distinct sequence sets acquired from the carotid artery of a volunteer, utilized for evaluating ultrasound imaging techniques.
dcterms:title: Additional in vivo dataset
